data.database_description: The database is designed to manage and track various aspects of a business operation focused on customer engagement, product management, and order fulfillment. It includes tables for storing information about premises, products available for sale, and customer details such as contact information and payment methods. The schema supports marketing efforts through mailshot campaigns targeted at specific customer segments and tracks the outcomes of these campaigns. Additionally, it manages customer addresses linked to their premises, records orders placed by customers along with shipping details, and logs individual order items including product specifics and delivery statuses. Relationships between tables are established using foreign keys, ensuring data integrity and facilitating complex queries for business analytics.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each premise.
Type of the premise (e.g., Warehouse, Residence).
Detailed information about the premises.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about different premises such as warehouses, residences, or offices.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each product.
Category to which the product belongs (e.g., Food, Electronics).
Name of the product offered for sale.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains information about products available for sale, including category and name.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each customer.
Preferred method of payment for the customer (e.g., Credit Card, Direct Debit).
Full name of the customer.
Contact phone number for the customer.
Email address for communication with the customer.
Physical address of the customer, often linked to their premises.
Username or login identifier for accessing customer accounts.
Encrypted password for securing customer account access.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each mailshot campaign.
Category of products targeted by the mailshot campaign (e.g., food, clothes).
Name or code representing the mailshot campaign.
Start date and time for when the mailshot campaign was initiated.
End date and time marking the conclusion of the mailshot campaign.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores details about marketing campaigns sent via mailshots to target specific customer segments.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the associated customer.
Identifier for the associated premise.
Start date and time when the address became valid.
Type of address (e.g., Billing, Shipping).
End date and time when the address is no longer valid.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores customer address information linked to premises, including type and validity period.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each order.
Identifier linking the order to a specific customer in the Customers table.
Current status of the order (e.g., Cancelled, Delivered).
Shipping method used for delivering the order (e.g., FedEx, UPS).
Date and time when the order was placed.
Date and time when the order was delivered.
Cost associated with shipping the order.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about orders placed by customers, including order status and shipping details.

columns.columnDescription: Reference to the specific mailshot campaign associated with this record.
Unique identifier for customers who received the mailshot.
Result of the mailshot interaction, such as 'Order' or 'No Response'.
Date and time when the customer's response to the mailshot was recorded.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks customer interactions with mailshot campaigns, recording outcomes and response dates.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each order item.
Status of the order item (e.g., Delivered, Paid, Cancelled).
Identifier linking the item to a specific customer order.
Identifier linking the item to a specific product.
Condition status of the item (e.g., good, damaged).
Timestamp when the item was delivered.
Quantity of this specific product ordered in the order.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores detailed information about each item within an order, including status and delivery details.
